# tom.Quest

**AGENT REQUIREMENT: After ANY code change, add/update relevant info here. After ANY bug fix, add to Fixes section. If you make ANY command mistake or environment issue, add to Shell Reminders. This prevents repeated mistakes and keeps context accurate.**

## Rules
- After making changes, give me a commit message to use that describes what was changed. 
- always style the site name as tom.Quest
- avoid number input spinners; use text inputs for numeric intervals
- never implement auto-scrolling that moves the user unexpectedly (e.g. chat page)
- maintain comprehensive debug logs when creating/modifying code
- One-time DB changes (SQL/RLS/migrations): paste the SQL in chat for me to run; don't put large one-off SQL blocks in code comments.
- Debug logs: avoid logging large response bodies (use `debugFetch(..., { logResponseBody: false })` for large JSON like `/data/*.json`); only log full payloads for errors.

## Shell Reminders (Windows PowerShell)
- NO `&&` chaining: use `;` or separate commands
- NO heredoc `<<'EOF'`: use simple `-m "message"` for commits
- Use `working_directory` param instead of `cd`
- rg tool can fail with absolute paths; omit path for root search
- Glob tool can fail with Windows absolute `target_directory`; omit it (or use forward-slash paths)
- `npx tsc --noEmit` can fail on stale `.next/dev/types`; rely on `npm run lint` unless `.next` has been regenerated
- If `npm run lint` fails with `eslint: not found`, install deps first (`npm install`) (confirmed again 2026-02-22)
- `npm run lint` can fail on pre-existing issues in `app/boolback/DatasetReviewTab.tsx` (`no-explicit-any`) and `app/cube/page.tsx` (`react/no-unescaped-entities`); treat as baseline unless touched
- `npm run build` can fail on stale `.next/dev/types/validator.ts` referencing removed routes; delete `.next` and rerun
- Before Vercel deploys, run `npm run build`; `npm run lint` and `npm test` can both pass while Next.js production TypeScript still fails on stricter app-route compilation
- `vercel env add <NAME> preview --value ...` can return `git_branch_required` in non-interactive runs; if it does, add preview envs via the Vercel dashboard/API or pass an explicit preview branch
- `vercel env add <NAME> production --value ...` can succeed and then hang without exiting; if the success message is already printed, kill the stuck process and continue
- Use `ReadFile` (not `Read`) and ensure tool JSON is valid before sending
- Python `-c` one-liners cannot include inline `def` after semicolons; use lambda or a real script block
- Python `-c` one-liners also break easily when you try to smuggle escaped newlines like `\ntry:` through shell quoting; use a real script block or `curl` instead
- Shell tool can return `Command failed to spawn: Aborted` on larger heredoc requests; rerun with a shorter script
- `ReadLints` can timeout even with scoped paths; rerun once, then validate edited files with `npm run lint` if needed
- Some Linux/Turing shells do not have `rg`; use Cursor `rg` tool for code search and `awk`/`python` for shell-side process filtering
- Turing shell process inspection can fail with `rg: command not found`; use `ps -ef | awk ...` instead of shell `rg`
- `openclaw devices pending` is not a valid CLI subcommand in current OpenClaw; use `openclaw devices list`
- `vitest run` exits with code 1 when no tests exist; for initial test setup either add the first test before running or use `--passWithNoTests` intentionally
- Red-phase Vitest imports fail during Vite import analysis when the target module file does not exist yet; create the file stub first if you need the suite to execute individual tests instead of failing at module resolution
- With Vitest fake timers, attach the rejection expectation before advancing the clock for timeout tests; otherwise Vitest can report an unhandled rejection even when the test logic is correct
- Current ESLint config flags synchronous `setState` work inside effects via `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`; move loading/reset state into callbacks or async tasks instead of calling setters directly in the effect body
- `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect` also flags direct state reset branches like `if (!url) setConnection(null)` inside effects; derive null state from props/render when possible instead of mutating it in the effect body
- `react-hooks/immutability` flags mutating memoized class instances after `useMemo`; pass mutable callbacks like `onStateChange` through constructor options instead of assigning properties inside an effect

